pe":"text","url":"/docs/components/icon#available-slot-overrides","content":"**`icon.content`**: Overrides the BentoIllustration component - affects SVG transformations (rotate, flip), accessibility attributes (`role`, `focusable`, `aria-labelledby`), viewBox calculations, and final SVG element rendering"},"462":{"id":"/docs/components/icon-57","page_id":"/docs/components/icon","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/icon#available-slot-overrides","content":"For complete slot override patterns and examples, see the `@bento/slots` package documentation."},"463":{"id":"/docs/components/icon-58","page_id":"/docs/components/icon","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/icon#custom-icons","content":"While the Icon component loads design system approved icons from the CDN by default, teams can introduce custom icons using the underlying Bento Icon system."},"464":{"id":"/docs/components/icon-59","page_id":"/docs/components/icon","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/icon#adding-icons-synchronously","content":"Use the `set` method to add custom icons that are available immediately:"},"465":{"id":"/docs/components/icon-60","page_id":"/docs/components/icon","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/icon#adding-icons-asynchronously","content":"Use the `ondemand` method to load custom icons from your own sources:"},"466":{"id":"/docs/components/icon-61","page_id":"/docs/components/icon","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/icon#custom-icon-apis","content":"The following methods are exported from `@godaddy/antares` for custom icon management:"},"467":{"id":"/docs/components/icon-62","page_id":"/docs/components/icon","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/icon#custom-icon-apis","content":"**`set(icons)`**: Synchronously add icons to the store"},"468":{"id":"/docs/components/icon-63","page_id":"/docs/components/icon","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/icon#custom-icon-apis","content":"**`ondemand(loader)`**: Register an asynchronous icon loader (returns unregister function)"},"469":{"id":"/docs/components/icon-64","page_id":"/docs/components/icon","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/icon#custom-icon-apis","content":"**`parser(svgString)`**: Parse SVG strings into React elements"},"470":{"id":"/docs/components/icon-65","page_id":"/docs/components/icon","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/icon#custom-icon-apis","content":"These are re-exports of the underlying Bento Icon system methods. For complete API documentation, advanced usage patterns, and implementation details, see the `@bento/icon` and `@bento/svg-parser` package documentation."},"471":{"id":"/docs/components/icon-66","page_id":"/docs/components/icon","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/icon#notes","content":"Custom icons integrate seamlessly with all Icon component features (transformations, accessibility, sprite mode, etc.)"},"472":{"id":"/docs/components/icon-67","page_id":"/docs/components/icon","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/icon#notes","content":"Multiple `ondemand` loaders can be registered and will be called in order until one returns content"},"473":{"id":"/docs/components/icon-68","page_id":"/docs/components/icon","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/icon#notes","content":"Use the `parser` function to convert SVG strings to React elements"},"474":{"id":"/docs/components/icon-69","page_id":"/docs/components/icon","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/icon#notes","content":"Custom icons are cached automatically just like CDN icons"},"475":{"id":"/docs/components/icon-70","page_id":"/docs/components/icon","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/icon#css-classes","content":"The component accepts standard `className` and `style` props:"},"476":{"id":"/docs/components/icon-71","page_id":"/docs/components/icon","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/icon#css-classes","content":"**Important**: When you supply a `className`, you