orative-icons","content":"Decorative icons"},"953":{"id":"/docs/components/tag-14","page_id":"/docs/components/tag","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/tag#indicator-dot","content":"Indicator dot"},"954":{"id":"/docs/components/tag-15","page_id":"/docs/components/tag","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/tag#best-practices","content":"Best Practices"},"955":{"id":"/docs/components/tag-16","page_id":"/docs/components/tag","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/tag#when-to-use","content":"When to Use"},"956":{"id":"/docs/components/tag-17","page_id":"/docs/components/tag","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/tag#when-not-to-use","content":"When Not to Use"},"957":{"id":"/docs/components/tag-18","page_id":"/docs/components/tag","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/tag#basic","content":"A minimal tag with the default emphasis and size."},"958":{"id":"/docs/components/tag-19","page_id":"/docs/components/tag","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/tag#emphasis","content":"Nine emphasis options are available. Choose the one that fits the visual tone of your context."},"959":{"id":"/docs/components/tag-20","page_id":"/docs/components/tag","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/tag#sizes","content":"Choose a size that fits the surrounding content. Smaller tags work well in compact layouts like tables; larger tags suit headings or hero sections."},"960":{"id":"/docs/components/tag-21","page_id":"/docs/components/tag","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/tag#inline","content":"Use `design=\"inline\"` to embed a tag within a sentence. The background and border are removed so the tag blends into the text flow."},"961":{"id":"/docs/components/tag-22","page_id":"/docs/components/tag","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/tag#high-contrast","content":"A bolder color treatment for when tags need to stand out more — for example, on colored backgrounds."},"962":{"id":"/docs/components/tag-23","page_id":"/docs/components/tag","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/tag#with-icon","content":"Icons reinforce the tag's meaning at a glance. Add an `Icon` as a child — it inherits the tag's color and scales with its size."},"963":{"id":"/docs/components/tag-24","page_id":"/docs/components/tag","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/tag#indicator","content":"A minimal style that pairs a small colored dot with a neutral background. Well suited for dense layouts like tables or dashboards where multiple tags in close proximity would otherwise compete for attention."},"964":{"id":"/docs/components/tag-25","page_id":"/docs/components/tag","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/tag#screen-readers","content":"Tags are `<span>` elements with no special ARIA role. Screen readers announce the tag's text as part of normal page content — no extra markup is needed."},"965":{"id":"/docs/components/tag-26","page_id":"/docs/components/tag","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/tag#decorative-icons","content":"Icons passed as children must include `aria-hidden=\"true\"` so they are skipped by screen readers. The text label is the sole carrier of meaning."},"966":{"id":"/docs/components/tag-27","page_id":"/docs/components/tag","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/tag#indicator-dot","content":"The colored dot is decorative and invisible to screen readers. The text label must convey the status on its own — never rely on the dot alone to communicate meaning."},"967":{"id":"/docs/components/tag-28","page_id":"/docs/components/tag","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/tag#best-practices","content":"Use the indicator style in dense layouts like tables and dashboards. Use the filled style when the tag is a prominent, standalone element on a card or hero section."},"968":{"id":"/docs/components/tag-29","page_id":"/docs/components/tag","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/tag#best-practices","content":"Default to the small size in compact layouts like tables and lists. Use medium or large only when the tag needs to stand out as a primary piece of information."},"969":{"id":"/docs/components/tag-30","page_id":"/docs/components/tag","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/tag#best-practices","content":"Use the inline design only within running prose. In grouped or standalone contexts, the filled style provides better visual separation."},"970":{"id":"/docs/components/tag-31","page_id":"/docs/components/tag","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/tag#best-practices","content":"Do not stack multiple tags of different emphasis on the same item. Choose the most important one — too many competing labels lose their meaning."},"971":{"id":"/docs/components/tag-32","page_id":"/docs/components/tag","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/tag#when-to-use","content":"Showing the status of an item on a card, table row, or list entry (e.g. \"Active\", \"Expired\", \"Pending\")"},"972":{"id":"/docs/components/tag-33","page_id":"/docs/components/tag","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/tag#when-to-use","content":"Categorizing or grouping content so users can scan and filter quickly (e.g. \"New\", \"Sale\", \"Beta\")"},"973":{"id":"/docs/components/tag-34","page_id":"/docs/components/tag","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/tag#when-to-use","content":"Surfacing metadata about an item (e.g. \"Pro\", \"Free trial\", \"Internal\")"},"974":{"id":"/docs/components/tag-35","page_id":"/docs/components/tag","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/tag#when-to-use","content":"Communicating priority or category in project management and collaboration tools (e.g. \"High priority\", \"In review\")"},"975":{"id":"/docs/components/tag-36","page_id":"/docs/components/tag","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/tag#when-not-to-use","content":"If users need to click or dismiss it — use a **Button** instead."},"976":{"id":"/docs/components/tag-37","page_id":"/docs/components/tag","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/tag#when-not-to-use","content":"If the label is part of a sentence with no visual distinction — just use text."},"977":{"id":"/docs/components/text","page_id":"/docs/components/text","type":"page","content":"Text","breadcrumbs":["Docs","Components"],"tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/text"},"978":{"id":"/docs/components/text-0","page_id":"/docs/components/text","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/text","content":"Text component for displaying and formatting text content with alignment and truncation options"},"979":{"id":"/docs/components/text-1","page_id":"/docs/components/text","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/text#installation","content":"Installation"},"980":{"id":"/docs/components/text-2","page_id":"/docs/components/text","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/text#props","content":"Props"},"981":{"id":"/docs/components/text-3","page_id":"/docs/components/text","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/text#examples","content":"Examples"},"982":{"id":"/docs/components/text-4","page_id":"/docs/components/text","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/text#as","content":"As"},"983":{"id":"/docs/components/text-5","page_id":"/docs/components/text","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/text#align","content":"Align"},"984":{"id":"/docs/components/text-6","page_id":"/docs/components/text","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/text#max-lines","content":"Max Lines"},"985":{"id":"/docs/components/text-7","page_id":"/docs/components/text","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/text#wrap","content":"Wrap"},"986":{"id":"/docs/components/text-8","page_id":"/docs/components/text","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/text","content":"The `Text` component prepares content with a few properties."},"987":{"id":"/docs/components/text-9","page_id":"/docs/components/text","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/text#props","content":"The `Text` component accepts the following props:"},"988":{"id":"/docs/components/text-10","page_id":"/docs/components/text","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/text#as","content":"Setting the `as` prop allows you to change the HTML tag of the `Text` component."},"989":{"id":"/docs/components/text-11","page_id":"/docs/components/text","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/text#align","content":"Setting the `align` prop allows you to change the alignment of the text. You can choose from `start`, `center`, `end`, or `justify`.\n`start` works like `left` and `end` works like `right`. These keywords support RTL languages so you do not need to worry about the language of the text."},"990":{"id":"/docs/components/text-12","page_id":"/docs/components/text","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/text#max-lines","content":"Setting the `maxLines` prop allows you to limit the number of lines of text that are displayed using an ellipsis. In browsers that don't support multiline text truncation using `line-clamp`, the text will be truncated after a single line regardless of the number provided for `maxLines`."},"991":{"id":"/docs/components/text-13","page_id":"/docs/components/text","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/text#wrap","content":"Setting the `wrap` prop allows you to change the wrapping of the text. The values can be `wrap`, `nowrap`, `balance`, `pretty`, or `stable`."},"992":{"id":"/docs/components/text-14","page_id":"/docs/components/text","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/text#wrap","content":"`wrap` is the setting that is most commonly used. For most elements you will not to explicitly set this."},"993":{"id":"/docs/components/text-15","page_id":"/docs/components/text","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/text#wrap","content":"`nowrap` should be avoided except in cases where it is important to prevent the text from wrapping."},"994":{"id":"/docs/components/text-16","page_id":"/docs/components/text","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/text#wrap","content":"`balance` is most commonly used for headlines, titles, and labels."},"995":{"id":"/docs/components/text-17","page_id":"/docs/components/text","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/text#wrap","content":"`pretty` is most commonly used for body text."},"996":{"id":"/docs/components/text-18","page_id":"/docs/components/text","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/text#wrap","content":"`stable` is commonly used for editable text, such as textareas."},"997":{"id":"/docs/components/toggle-button","page_id":"/docs/components/toggle-button","type":"page","content":"ToggleButton","breadcrumbs":["Docs","Components"],"tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/toggle-button"},"998":{"id":"/docs/components/toggle-button-0","page_id":"/docs/components/toggle-button","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/toggle-button","content":"Accessible toggle button component for grouped contextual actions with single or multiple selection, keyboard navigation, and RTL-aware layouts."},"999":{"id":"/docs/components/toggle-button-1","page_id":"/docs/components/toggle-button","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/toggle-button#installation","content":"Installation"},"1000":{"id":"/docs/components/toggle-button-2","page_id":"/docs/components/toggle-button","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/toggle-button#props","content":"Props"},"1001":{"id":"/docs/components/toggle-button-3","page_id":"/docs/components/toggle-button","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/toggle-button#examples","content":"Examples"},"1002":{"id":"/docs/components/toggle-button-4","page_id":"/docs/components/toggle-button","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/toggle-button#default-single-selection","content":"Default (Single Selection)"},"1003":{"id":"/docs/components/toggle-button-5","page_id":"/docs/components/toggle-button","ty